name: chicagotribune
text:
“People are like, 'Oh, it must be so healing to write these songs.' It’s clarifying, it’s empowering, but it doesn’t necessarily heal the relationship itself.”

Alanis Morissette in conversation with Liz Phair: https://t.co/xarjC0jS7Q

name: chicagotribune
text: Three Chicago police officers and a suspect in a carjacking were injured in an exchange of gunfire outside a Northwest Side police station Thursday morning, apparently after the suspect concealed a weapon during his arrest, several sources told the Tribune https://t.co/dgmmlA0FHE

name: chicagotribune
text: RT @MarySchmich: John Lewis’ funeral was a few hours of hope, away from the doomsday world. Thoughts provoked by watching that beautiful funeral while toggling back and forth between Ebenezer Baptist Church and Twitter. Today's column. https://t.co/0DVlwsfRzu
